### Al-Munir Consultancy API Examples
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000/api/v1

### 1. Register new user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "+923001234567",
  "cnic": "12345-6789012-3",
  "address": "123 Main Street, Lahore",
  "city": "Lahore",
  "sponsor_referral_code": ""
}

### 2. Login user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get user profile (requires authentication)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Register with referral code
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Jane",
  "last_name": "Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "+923001234568",
  "cnic": "12345-6789012-4",
  "address": "456 Oak Street, Karachi",
  "city": "Karachi",
  "sponsor_referral_code": "ABC123"
}

### 5. Get all Consultant (Admin only)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/Consultant?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Search Consultant (Admin/Manager only)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/Consultant/search?q=john&page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 7. Get team structure
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/Consultant/USER_ID/team-structure?depth=3
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 8. Get team statistics
GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/Consultant/USER_ID/team-stats
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 9. Update user profile
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/v1/Consultant/profile
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "first_name": "Updated John",
  "phone": "+923001234569",
  "address": "Updated address"
}

### 10. Update user status (Admin only)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/v1/Consultant/USER_ID/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "status": "active"
}

### 11. Update user level (Admin only)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/v1/Consultant/USER_ID/level
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "level": 3
}

### 12. Change password
PATCH http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/change-password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "current_password": "password123",
  "new_password": "newpassword123"
}

### 13. Forgot password
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com"
}

### 14. Reset password
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "RESET_TOKEN_FROM_FORGOT_PASSWORD",
  "new_password": "resetpassword123"
}

### 15. Logout
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Notes:
### - Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE with actual JWT token from login response
### - Replace USER_ID with actual user UUID
### - Some endpoints require specific roles (Admin, Manager, etc.)
### - Update .env file with correct database credentials before testing
